`sources/` is the better name. It makes the layer boundary clearer. If you later want a place for truly messy pre-ingest drops, I’d use something like `inbox/` or `captures/` for that, and keep `sources/` as “immutable source corpus.”

**`wq.py`**
- I would not make `WHERE wiki = ...` the default mental model.
- Each `wikis/<slug>/` should behave like its own database. In practice that means `wq.py` should usually be scoped to one workspace root via `--dir`, not to the whole repo. The current `--dir` flag already points in that direction at [wq.py](/Users/giladbarnea/dev/autowiki/wq.py#L318).
- If you later want cross-workspace querying, add a normal derived column like `workspace` or `workspace_slug`, not `wiki`. `wiki` is overloaded now that `wiki/` is also the maintained subtree.
- I’d also add a normal `collection` column in that advanced mode: `wiki`, `sources`, `meta`.
- `text` should remain the only truly “magic” column, because it changes rendering behavior. A workspace column would just be ordinary metadata.

There’s also an important behavioral point here: once you rename `raw/` to `sources/`, `wq.py` probably should not query `sources/` by default. Q&A is supposed to happen over the maintained wiki, not over the raw source pile. Right now `wq.py` blindly loads every frontmatter document under the scanned root at [wq.py](/Users/giladbarnea/dev/autowiki/wq.py#L96), so it would need a workspace-aware inclusion policy.

**Hook + `src/autowiki`**
- The biggest shift is that the system needs a first-class notion of “workspace root.” Right now everything is written as if “repo root = one wiki.”
- The pre-commit hook currently regenerates one repo-level `index.md` for the whole repo at [.githooks/pre-commit](/Users/giladbarnea/dev/autowiki/.githooks/pre-commit#L13). In a multi-wiki setup, that should become “find affected workspaces, then regenerate each `wikis/<slug>/index.md`.” The current copy-back to root `index.md` at [.githooks/pre-commit](/Users/giladbarnea/dev/autowiki/.githooks/pre-commit#L15) no longer matches the model.
- The CLI also encodes the old assumption by naming the target `--repo-root` in [cli.py](/Users/giladbarnea/dev/autowiki/src/autowiki/cli.py#L29). Behaviorally, this wants to become `--workspace-root`, plus maybe a separate “generate all workspace indexes” command later.
- Validation is currently too broad. `should_validate_markdown_path()` in [frontmatter_validation.py](/Users/giladbarnea/dev/autowiki/src/autowiki/frontmatter_validation.py#L80) will try to validate any staged `.md` that isn’t hidden or a root README/AGENTS. In a multi-wiki design, that would wrongly enforce strict wiki frontmatter on `sources/**/*.md` if those sources happen to be markdown.
